        "logic_path": "Offline_File_Transfer",
        "specification": {
          "function": "1. Time Unit: 1 unit = 1 second (1000ms). \n2. Internal Components: The model encapsulates a Sender, Server (ServerReceiver + StorageQueue + ServerSender), Receiver, and four Subnets (A1, A2, B1, B2).\n3. Subnet Logic: All subnets (A1, A2, B1, B2) are FIFO and impose a fixed 3s delay on any packet/ACK passing through.\n4. Sender Logic:\n    - Maintain `total_packets_to_send` and `current_bit` (starts at 0).\n    - Upon `control N`: Increment `total_packets_to_send`. If idle, start preparation.\n    - Preparation: 10s delay before sending a new packet.\n    - ABP: Send Packet(seq, bit). Start 20s timeout timer.\n    - On ACK(bit) == current_bit: Stop timer, flip `current_bit`, decrement `total_packets_to_send`, and if > 0, repeat preparation.\n    - On Timeout: Retransmit current Packet(seq, bit) and restart 20s timer.\n5. ServerReceiver Logic:\n    - On packet arrival: Wait 3s processing delay.\n    - If packet_bit == expected_bit: Push to StorageQueue, send ACK(expected_bit) to SubnetA2, flip expected_bit.\n    - If packet_bit != expected_bit: Send ACK(previous_bit) to SubnetA2.\n6. ServerSender Logic:\n    - Condition to send: `download_allowed` is True AND StorageQueue is not empty AND not waiting for an ACK.\n    - Action: Pop packet from queue, send to SubnetB1, start ABP cycle.\n    - Valve: If `download_allowed` becomes False during a cycle, it must complete the current packet-ACK exchange before stopping.\n7. Receiver Logic:\n    - On packet arrival: 10s processing delay (simulating slow write).\n    - After delay: Send ACK(bit) back via SubnetB2.",
          "logging": "The model must log the following events to the internal logger:\n1. Sender: 'control_cmd' (added, total_remaining), 'preparation_started' (duration=10000), 'packet_sent' (seq, bit, is_retry), 'ack_received' (bit), 'timeout' (seq).\n2. ServerReceiver: 'packet_received' (seq, bit), 'ack_sent_to_sender' (bit).\n3. ServerSender: 'download_valve_change' (allowed), 'packet_forwarded' (seq, bit), 'ack_received_from_receiver' (bit).\n4. Receiver: 'processing_started' (seq, duration=10000), 'ack_sent' (bit).\nAll logs must include 'timestamp_ms' (simulation time in ms) and the specific 'model' name string as per requirements.",
